## Contract E — WebSocket messages

Shared envelope on **both** sockets:
```json
{ "type": "namespace:event", "payload": { } }
```

### E.1 Chat socket — `/ws/chat` (hosted by the API, owned by C, consumed by D)

Client → Server:
```
auth            { token }
message:send    { to: <userId|null>, content }     // null `to` = lobby
typing          { to }
read            { messageId }
```
Server → Client:
```
auth:ok | auth:error
message:new     { id, from, to, content, ts }
presence:update { userId, online: bool }
typing          { from }
notification    { kind: "game_invite"|"tournament", data: { ... } }   // advanced chat
```
Blocks are enforced **server-side** before relaying any `message:new`.